<H2>Statistical Genetics Group Software available</H2>

<P>Below is a list of software by members of the Statistical Genetics
Group at the University of Reading, plus
details of supporting literature if appropriate. Depending
on your browser, to download a file either left-click on the name 
of the program (underlined), or right-click on that name and
select the option "Save Target As ...".</P>

<CENTER>
<TABLE WIDTH="96%" BORDER="1" CELLPADDING="5" CELLSPACING="0" BGCOLOR="#EFEFEF">
<TR BGCOLOR="#DFDFDF"><TD ALIGN="CENTER" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2">
<B>API-CALC 1.0</B>
</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>
Programme for calculating the probability of identification in the
presence of given degrees of relatedness in the population, inbreeding
and coancestry
</TD>
<TD><B>Contact</B>:
<A HREF="mailto:A.D.J.Overall&#064;brighton.ac.uk">A.D.J.Overall&#064;brighton.ac.uk</A>
</TD></TR>
<TR><TD COLSPAN="2">
Programme written by: A.D.J. Overall
</TD></TR>
<TR><TD COLSPAN="2">
K.L. Ayres &amp; A.D.J. Overall (2004).
API-CALC 1.0: a computer program for calculating the average probability of identity allowing for substructure, inbreeding and the presence of close relatives. 
<I>Molecular Ecology Notes</I> <B>4</B>, 315-318. 
</TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="CENTER">
<A HREF="./software/apicalc/API-CALC.zip" target="_parent">API-CALC.zip</A>
<BR>(Updated June 2004, for input problems)
</TD>
<TD WIDTH="30%"><B>Distributed as:</B>
Zipped file containing PC executable, plus test files
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</CENTER>

<BR>

<CENTER>
<TABLE WIDTH="96%" BORDER="1" CELLPADDING="5" CELLSPACING="0" BGCOLOR="#EFEFEF">
<TR BGCOLOR="#DFDFDF"><TD ALIGN="CENTER" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2">
<B>BAYESFST</B>
</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>
Bayesian estimation of the coancestry coefficient <I>F</I><SUB>ST</SUB>
</TD>
<TD><B>Contact</B>:
<A HREF="mailto:d.balding&#064;ic.ac.uk">d.balding&#064;ic.ac.uk</A>
</TD></TR>
<TR><TD COLSPAN="2">
Programme written by: D.J. Balding, K.L. Ayres, M.A. Beaumont, P.O'Reilly
</TD></TR>
<TR><TD COLSPAN="2">
D.J. Balding (2003).
Likelihood-based inference for genetic correlation coefficients.
<I>Theoretical Population Biology</I>, <B>63</B>: 221-230
<BR>and<BR>
M.A. Beaumont & D.J. Balding (2004)
Identifying adaptive genetic divergence among populations from genome
scans. <I>Molecular Ecology</I>, <B>13</B>: 969-980, 2004
</TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="CENTER">
<A HREF="./software/bayesfst/bayesfst.c">bayesfst.c</A>,
<A HREF="./software/bayesfst/INTFILE">INTFILE</A>,
<A HREF="./software/bayesfst/myutil.c">myutil.c</A>,
<A HREF="./software/bayesfst/myutil.h">myutil.h</A>
<BR>Example dataset <A HREF="./software/bayesfst/data_BB04.inp">data_BB04.inp</A> 
now available (flies data from Beaumont &amp; Balding, 2004)
<BR>Further files and R scripts available in the file
<A HREF="http://www.rubic.reading.ac.uk/~mab/stuff/bayesfst_extras.zip">bayesfst_extras.zip</A>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH="30%"><B>Distributed as:</B>
ANSI C source code
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</CENTER>

<BR>

<CENTER>
<TABLE WIDTH="96%" BORDER="1" CELLPADDING="5" CELLSPACING="0" BGCOLOR="#EFEFEF">
