<TABLE WIDTH="96%" BORDER="1" CELLPADDING="5" CELLSPACING="0" BGCOLOR="#EFEFEF">
<TR BGCOLOR="#DFDFDF"><TD ALIGN="CENTER" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2">
<B>MAC5</B>
</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>
A package implementing MCMC sampling of phylogenetic trees using
five-state models of nucleotide substitution
</TD>
<TD><B>Contact</B>:
<A HREF="mailto:webmaster&#064;agapow.net">webmaster&#064;agapow.net</A>
</TD></TR>
<TR><TD COLSPAN="2">
Programme written by: G. McGuire, P.M. Agapow
</TD></TR>
<TR><TD COLSPAN="2">
G. McGuire, M.C. Denham &amp; D. J. Balding (2001) 
Models of evolution for DNA sequences including gaps 
<I>Molecular Biology and Evolution</I> <B>18</B>, 481 - 490
</TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="CENTER">
From URL: 
<A HREF="http://www.agapow.net/software/mac5/" target="_parent">http://www.agapow.net/software/mac5/</A>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH="30%"><B>Distributed as:</B>
TAR file, also other Mac and Windows binaries
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</CENTER>

